# Backend Environment Configuration
# Copy this file to .env and customize for your environment

# =============================================================================
# AI Configuration
# =============================================================================

# Default AI difficulty level for new sessions
# Options: beginner, intermediate, advanced, expert
#
# SMART DEFAULT (recommended): Leave commented out for auto-detection
#   - If DDS is available (production/Linux): automatically uses 'expert' (9/10)
#   - If DDS not available (dev/macOS M1/M2): automatically uses 'advanced' (8/10)
#   - This prevents DDS crashes on macOS while maximizing AI quality on production
#
# Development (macOS M1/M2):
#   - Auto-detects to 'advanced' (no DDS crashes, still strong 8/10 gameplay)
#   - Can manually override to 'intermediate' if needed for testing
#
# Production (Oracle Cloud ARM Linux with DDS):
#   - Auto-detects to 'expert' (uses DDS for 9/10 perfect play)
#   - Set explicitly to 'expert' in production .env to be certain
#
# DEFAULT_AI_DIFFICULTY=advanced  # Uncomment to force specific level

# =============================================================================
# Production Deployment
# =============================================================================
# For production deployment, set:
# DEFAULT_AI_DIFFICULTY=expert
#
# This gives users the best AI experience by default while still allowing
# them to adjust the difficulty level through the UI if needed.

# =============================================================================
# Email Notifications (for Review Requests)
# =============================================================================
# To receive email notifications when users submit review requests:
#
# 1. Use a Gmail account with 2-Factor Authentication enabled
# 2. Generate an App Password at: https://myaccount.google.com/apppasswords
# 3. Set the following environment variables:
#
# EMAIL_SENDER=your-email@gmail.com
# EMAIL_PASSWORD=your-16-char-app-password
# EMAIL_RECIPIENT=where-to-send@example.com  # Optional, defaults to EMAIL_SENDER
# APP_URL=https://app.mybridgebuddy.com      # For links in emails
